First, I'll try talking with Chris again.

101
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:23,410
Yes, thank you.

102
00:13:39,990 --> 00:13:41,780
 Yes? 

103
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:46,170
 - You're here? 
- Oh, Joon Young.

104
00:13:46,170 --> 00:13:48,500
Hello.

105
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:49,950
What are you doing at the door?

106
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:53,380
This is reporter Lee Doo Ri. You know her, right?

107
00:13:55,450 --> 00:13:57,830
- "Help"? 
- Yes.

108
00:13:57,830 --> 00:14:04,060
I want to know what the professor taught you that was the biggest help in making you the "competition killer".

109
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:12,640
Professor Yoo knows the subject of piano competitions better than anyone else.

110
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,220
As expected...

111
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:20,170
You've certainly earned your nickname the "animal tamer".

112
00:14:22,150 --> 00:14:26,820
Among Seoryeong University professors, you're uniquely not an alumnus.

113
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:29,590
You must have run into many difficulties because of it,

114
00:14:29,590 --> 00:14:35,060
but through Joon Young, many of your apprentices have shown amazing work in competitions as a result.

115
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:40,400
It's not like the professor's name is credited in music, so why does it matter?

116
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,290
Now, wouldn't they be accredited?

117
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:44,620
It's written in length with every profile.

118
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:47,370
Which school and under which professor they studied.

119
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:50,590
This is the common thread of music schools.

120
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:55,480
But... after asking, I realized it was a dumb question.

121
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:59,860
With Joon Young, we can clearly call this the beginning of Yoo Tae Jin's line, yes?

122
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:02,520
Oh, don't be silly. There's no "line".

123
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:07,520
But following the Chopin Competition,

124
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:11,070
I heard that the relationship between you two soured.

125
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:13,640
Oh you people, really...

126
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:18,290
People are spreading so many rumors just because they're jealous of Joon Young's success.

127
00:15:18,950 --> 00:15:24,160
Right? I mean, this is a community filled with envy.

128
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:27,550
People speak so childishly of your relationship to Joon Young.

129
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:30,260
That you lucked into him.

130
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:32,180
Ugh, really...

131
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,020
Now... shall we slowly wrap things up?

132
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:38,570
Shall we?

133
00:15:38,570 --> 00:15:40,850
Oh my, how the time flies.

134
00:15:40,850 --> 00:15:44,590
Then, let me ask one more question.

135
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:48,060
The Tchaikovsky competition will be held in a few months, right?

136
00:15:48,060 --> 00:15:50,490
Who do you think will win?

137
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:56,910
 Seung Ji Min won Chopin's 

138
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:59,840
 Which is why the rest of the decent competitors 

139
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,750
are all preparing for next year's Tchaikovsky's.

140
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:07,030
Because Tchaikovsky's never had a Korean winner.

141
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:10,260
Getting the first title is important, right?

142
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:15,000
So. Who is the person Park Joon Young expects to clinch the title?

143
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:25,690
Won't the person who's able to score highest amongst all judges win?

144
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:31,360
 That's true. Another dumb question. Sorry! 

145
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,530
 Let's finish here. 

146
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,920
Professor, thank you for setting aside time for me today.

147
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,370
Oh, nothing at all. I should thank you.

148
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:41,880
Joon Young, let's meet again.

149
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:51,340
Your... interviewing skills have grown a lot.

150
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:55,890
But why didn't you tell her you were participating in the Tchaikovsky competition?

151
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,080
What...

152
00:16:58,690 --> 00:17:01,880
are you afraid that you couldn't break even?

153
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:23,960
What are you doing?

154
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,780
What are you looking at so intently?

155
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:31,760
Oh, just the... class announcements.

156
00:17:35,410 --> 00:17:39,390
You look a little tired today.

157
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:43,810
No, I'm fine.

158
00:17:43,810 --> 00:17:46,780
Are you done with your classes?

159
00:17:46,780 --> 00:17:49,150
I just finished my lessons.

160
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:52,230
Oh, you must have been hard at work.

161
00:17:52,230 --> 00:17:54,120
What about lunch?

162
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:56,920
If you haven't had it yet, let's have it together.

163
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:04,210
What to do? I have another appointment outside so I need to go now.

164
00:18:04,210 --> 00:18:08,010
Ah. Are you seeing someone?

165
00:18:08,650 --> 00:18:12,600
Just... someone I know.

166
00:18:14,420 --> 00:18:16,600
I see.

167
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:22,070
Then... I'll get going.

168
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:23,900
Enjoy your lunch.

169
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:26,430
I will. You too.

170
00:18:26,430 --> 00:18:28,120
Yes.

