Oh, really? But you realize this is a fact, right?

186
00:20:11,350 --> 00:20:12,940
Right?

187
00:20:13,810 --> 00:20:16,030
It's not just between you and them,

188
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:18,960
there's a large gap between Jung Kyung and Hyeon Ho too.

189
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:22,740
- Please be more tactful with your wording. 
 - Which is why Park Joon Young...

190
00:20:24,610 --> 00:20:29,210
Even if you play in a chamber orchestra, play it with people who match your level.

191
00:20:29,210 --> 00:20:32,370
Those people I'll find for you.

192
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:36,090
Your career...

193
00:20:37,490 --> 00:20:41,000
You need to course-correct before it falls any further.

194
00:20:42,830 --> 00:20:44,710
Don't you think?

195
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,390
   

196
00:20:53,390 --> 00:20:55,210
 - Chae Song Ah.  
- Yes.

197
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:58,300
You can't be so shaky just because you're playing along with a piano.

198
00:20:58,300 --> 00:21:01,830
You have to maintain your own tempo as you play with the piano.

199
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:03,640
Ah, forgive me.

200
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:08,140
I had high expectations because you were a Seoryeong University student, but what's this?

201
00:21:10,350 --> 00:21:12,690
I'm sorry.

202
00:21:24,980 --> 00:21:27,260
Let's go together tomorrow morning. I'll call you.

203
00:21:27,260 --> 00:21:29,070
Thank you very much.

204
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:56,890
I came here to buy some sheet music.

205
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:59,640
Me too.

206
00:22:03,570 --> 00:22:06,020
I'll stop by next time.

207
00:22:06,020 --> 00:22:08,450
It's a small world.

208
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:16,120
We're going to keep running into each other. Are you going to avoid me every time?

209
00:22:17,290 --> 00:22:19,510
Just come in and buy your sheet music.

210
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:45,710
Do you by chance have any violin concerto songs?

211
00:22:45,710 --> 00:22:47,430
 Yes. 

212
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:51,200
Just a moment.

213
00:22:56,890 --> 00:22:58,600
Here it is.

214
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:00,160
Thank you.

215
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:02,800
Could you ring me up?

216
00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:12,950
Thank you.

217
00:23:15,590 --> 00:23:18,620
 I kept thinking to myself "What did I do wrong?" 

218
00:23:18,620 --> 00:23:21,380
 What did I miss that you left me? 

219
00:23:21,380 --> 00:23:23,780
 No matter what I think I... 

220
00:23:23,780 --> 00:23:26,760
 I haven't done a thing for 10 years besides chasing you. 

221
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:29,170
 Was that wrong? 

222
00:23:29,170 --> 00:23:36,550
♫   I guess you can't express everything with love    ♫
    

223
00:23:36,590 --> 00:23:41,290
♫   Those words of yours make me sad   ♫

224
00:23:41,290 --> 00:23:43,670
 - Give me what she has. 
 - Of course. 

225
00:23:43,670 --> 00:23:48,710
♫   You're leaving like this, but   ♫

226
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:51,940
♫   if you can be happy, that's enough for me  ♫

227
00:23:51,940 --> 00:23:55,490
 Take care! 

