00:27:03,090 --> 00:27:06,440
   

259
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:11,180
Dong Yoon canceled his blind date?

260
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:12,970
Yeah.

261
00:27:12,970 --> 00:27:16,990
Do you think... it's because of me?

262
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:20,270
Because he's thinking of me?

263
00:27:20,270 --> 00:27:26,340
 I'm sorry. But lately, I've been really busy. 

264
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:29,500
 Then, let's just have tea. 

265
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:31,930
Is something wrong?

266
00:27:31,930 --> 00:27:34,270
 I'll tell you when I see you. 

267
00:27:40,810 --> 00:27:46,210
Never mind. Let's stop talking about Yoon Dong Yoon.

268
00:27:47,430 --> 00:27:49,600
How are things going with you?

269
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:50,980
What do you mean?

270
00:27:50,980 --> 00:27:53,310
Park Joon Young!

271
00:27:54,390 --> 00:27:56,900
I don't know. I'm busy lately too.

272
00:27:56,900 --> 00:28:00,530
Because of the upcoming exams, I have to also get used to a new accompaniment.

273
00:28:00,530 --> 00:28:02,250
Accompaniment?

274
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:06,750
Yeah, the professor introduced me to a new pianist to play with.

275
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:14,010
- Why don't you... ask Park Joon Young to be your accompaniment?
 - Hmm?

276
00:28:14,010 --> 00:28:18,830
I mean, you're exploring your feelings with Joon Young, why are you looking for a pianist elsewhere?

277
00:28:18,830 --> 00:28:20,710
What?!

278
00:28:20,710 --> 00:28:24,660
No! No... that's a little too... um...

279
00:28:24,660 --> 00:28:27,050
A little too what?

280
00:28:27,620 --> 00:28:32,240
Well, that is... how would say, it's a little too...

281
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:35,440
There's too much of a difference.

282
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:40,200
For someone at his level to play an accompaniment for someone like me is just...

283
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:43,440
But also Joon Young is on his sabbatical.

284
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:47,130
- Chae Song Ah...
- Yeah?

285
00:28:47,130 --> 00:28:51,940
If he had feelings for you, do you think he'd bring up things like level differences or sabbaticals?

286
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:57,160
If a woman he liked asked him for it, he'd even play "Twinkle Twinkle Little Star".

287
00:28:57,160 --> 00:29:01,270
With an accompaniment like that, I'd even dance for it.

288
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:31,550
What are you doing?

289
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:33,080
Huh?

290
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:41,500
Oh, how have you been?

291
00:29:41,500 --> 00:29:43,090
 Yes. 

292
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:45,940
 Ah yes, yes. 

293
00:29:45,940 --> 00:29:49,410
Oh, but unfortunately, I don't think I can make my schedule work for that day.

294
00:29:50,020 --> 00:29:51,480
Yes, I'm sorry.

295
00:29:51,480 --> 00:29:54,540
Yes, that's fine. Let's try to meet next time.

296
00:29:54,540 --> 00:29:57,940
Yes, thank you. Have a nice day.

297
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:08,860
Just because I played an accompaniment for a student once. They think I'm some children's pianist.

298
00:30:08,860 --> 00:30:11,230
 Unbelievable. 

299
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:15,490
You too. Just because a girl you're seeing or any such person

300
00:30:15,490 --> 00:30:18,550
asks you for an accompaniment, don't even think about it.

301
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:22,990
When you play with lower-class players, you will lose your skill with them.

302
00:30:26,170 --> 00:30:28,570
It doesn't matter to me.

303
00:30:28,570 --> 00:30:31,710
It may not matter to you, but it probably matters to her.

304
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:39,690
She could practice all her life, but will never amount to more than your accompaniment.

305
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:44,840
What, you didn't think that far?

306
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:50,190
Even with romance, think about your class.

307
00:30:50,190 --> 00:30:52,840
Ruin comes in a moment.

308
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:56,880
Now let's try again with up-tempo.

309
00:31:09,750 --> 00:31:13,000
Did you enjoy your lessons?

310
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:16,440
Ah, yes... well...

311
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:26,760
What did you do today?

312
00:31:30,890 --> 00:31:35,140
I tried matching with an accompaniment for my grad school entrance exams.

313
00:31:37,250 --> 00:31:39,320
How was it?

314
00:31:41,290 --> 00:31:44,330
She was a little scary.

315
00:31:48,300 --> 00:31:53,490
 If he has feelings for you, do you think he'll bring up level differences or sabbaticals? 

316
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:04,960
The accompaniment is always important, but since this is the entrance exams...

317
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:11,650
The professor recommended I find an outstanding pianist.

318
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:18,660
I don't know if I can do well with this piano teacher...

319
00:32:18,660 --> 00:32:22,870
I'm... not entirely confident.

320
00:32:25,860 --> 00:32:31,470
 Even if she practiced her whole life she'll never amount to more than your accompaniment. 

321
00:32:32,220 --> 00:32:37,090
It's probably because it's your first time matching with her.

322
00:32:37,090 --> 00:32:39,730
Don't worry too much about it.

323
00:32:54,130 --> 00:32:56,500
Are you going home?

324
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:59,030
Yes. What about you?

325
00:32:59,030 --> 00:33:01,050
I'm  going to practice at school.

326
00:33:01,050 --> 00:33:03,740
There's a performance at Kyunghoo today.

327
00:33:05,770 --> 00:33:08,780
Then safe travels.

328
00:33:08,780 --> 00:33:10,530
Yes.

329
00:33:15,020 --> 00:33:18,260
When do you have classes tomorrow?

330
00:33:18,260 --> 00:33:19,720
I'm sorry?

331
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:23,120
Do you have time tomorrow at lunch?

332
00:33:25,620 --> 00:33:29,690
I'm not sure about lunch tomorrow.

333
00:33:29,690 --> 00:33:31,880
Oh, really?

334
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:35,080
Then call me tomorrow when you know.

335
00:33:36,950 --> 00:33:41,000
Yes. I'll do that.

336
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:48,810
♫   I'm reminded again of you who drifted away   ♫

337
00:33:48,810 --> 00:33:53,050
♫   though I loved you   ♫

338
00:33:55,620 --> 00:34:01,010
♫   The radiant memories of our past days  ♫

339
00:34:01,010 --> 00:34:08,300
♫   come visit me again   ♫

340
00:34:09,250 --> 00:34:16,130
♫   In the end, I wasn't able to forget anything about you   ♫

341
00:34:16,130 --> 00:34:21,460
♫   I must have loved you too much   ♫

342
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:29,360
♫   Because I miss you, I cry out your name   ♫

343
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,100
Why is this so hard?

344
00:34:31,100 --> 00:34:33,900
♫   Without you, I'm nothing   ♫

345
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:11,200
Yes, hello?

346
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:13,340
Yes, how have you been?

347
00:35:13,340 --> 00:35:15,970
You've been doing well?

348
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:21,380
I had completely forgotten. I'm sorry.

349
00:35:21,380 --> 00:35:25,840
In order to process your judge fees, I need your ID and the last four numbers of your account.

350
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:28,430
Yes, I'll send it right away.

351
00:35:28,430 --> 00:35:30,370
I'm sorry.

352
00:35:32,140 --> 00:35:34,330
Me? I'm doing well.

353
00:35:34,330 --> 00:35:37,470
It's still busy over there, right?

354
00:35:39,610 --> 00:35:41,310
Chairman Na?

355
00:35:41,310 --> 00:35:45,850
She suddenly fainted so we were similarly surprised.

356
00:35:45,850 --> 00:35:48,210
Thankfully I'm told she's gotten a lot better.

357
00:35:48,210 --> 00:35:51,880
I heard they're discharging her either today or tomorrow...

358
00:35:54,060 --> 00:35:55,970
Yes, yes.

359
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:59,330
Then, email me your ID and the last 4 of your account.

360
00:35:59,330 --> 00:36:01,520
Yes, thank you!

361
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:04,120
Deputy!

362
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:06,610
Ah, Deputy, how have you been!

363
00:36:06,610 --> 00:36:09,610
I missed you so much I thought I'd die.

364
00:36:25,330 --> 00:36:27,810
   

365
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:34,210
   

366
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:57,700
  - What the? 
 - Incredible!  

367
00:36:57,700 --> 00:37:01,640
 Really? Song Ah Noona and Park Joon Young Hyung are dating? 

368
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:09,150
- Unni. 
- Hmm?

369
00:37:09,150 --> 00:37:12,300
Are you going out with Park Joon  Young?

370
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:13,080
What?

371
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:15,240
There are rumors that you two are dating.

372
00:37:15,240 --> 00:37:18,210
I wondered... that last time when we ate, he was so...

373
00:37:18,210 --> 00:37:20,400
No.

374
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,620
It's not true?

375
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,880
It isn't.

376
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:32,360
See? Would a world-class musician meet with an ordinary music student?

377
00:37:33,620 --> 00:37:36,410
 Did she have to word it like that? 

378
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:47,100
What is it?

379
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:52,080
What are you looking at so intently?

380
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:55,050
Ah, it's just the class announcements.

381
00:37:59,210 --> 00:38:01,560
   

382
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:06,600
Song Ah!

383
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:19,680
Joon Young.

384
00:38:32,570 --> 00:38:36,700
I thought I wouldn't be able to see you because you were busy.

385
00:38:36,700 --> 00:38:39,410
Are you now all through with classes?

386
00:38:40,850 --> 00:38:42,620
Yes.

387
00:38:43,390 --> 00:38:47,270
Then... do you want to have dinner with me?

388
00:38:57,970 --> 00:39:03,880
A world-class artist playing with the last seat in the school orchestra...

389
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:11,800
would their levels never match in any circumstance?

390
00:39:17,780 --> 00:39:23,240
For some weird reason, there are a lot of people bringing up levels lately.

391
00:39:24,810 --> 00:39:27,990
I don't think about things like that.

392
00:39:27,990 --> 00:39:30,580
Then why did you tear it off?

393
00:39:31,580 --> 00:39:34,720
The orchestra seating list?

394
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:42,280
I didn't want you to fret over it.

395
00:39:43,330 --> 00:39:48,400
It's really... really a meaningless thing.

396
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:53,780
It looked like you would grow too attached and be hurt by it. And I didn't want that.

397
00:39:57,910 --> 00:40:00,860
The orchestra seats...

398
00:40:02,310 --> 00:40:04,850
are not meaningless.

399
00:40:05,740 --> 00:40:08,840
It's way too meaningful to me.

400
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:16,080
That's why I'm attached to it.

401
00:40:18,700 --> 00:40:26,320
If I was just one seat over. Just one row higher.

402
00:40:28,010 --> 00:40:31,310
I spent the last four years like that.

403
00:40:36,520 --> 00:40:38,630
You can't understand, can you?

404
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:43,610
You will probably never understand.

405
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:50,210
Which is why I—

406
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:59,440
Perhaps I... might never get a chance...

407
00:41:00,590 --> 00:41:05,450
to stand by your side.

408
00:41:09,890 --> 00:41:13,200
I'm losing confidence.

409
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:24,170
Then... why did you say you'd wait for me?

410
00:41:26,330 --> 00:41:31,620
Is that why you've pushed me away lately?

411
00:41:35,170 --> 00:41:41,060
Then why did you say things like "I like you" and "I'll wait for you?"

412
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:48,880
When I ask to eat with you, if you respond with, "Aren't our levels too different?,"

413
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:53,470
with answers like that...

414
00:41:53,470 --> 00:41:55,990
I can't come to you.

415
00:41:58,750 --> 00:42:02,530
I'm so sick and tired of hearing things like this.

416
00:42:04,090 --> 00:42:07,900
I don't want to hear that from you.

417
00:42:07,900 --> 00:42:10,720
I'm really sorry, but...

418
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:13,050
I'll leave first.

419
00:42:53,340 --> 00:42:57,870
   

420
00:43:21,530 --> 00:43:25,060
   

421
00:43:28,420 --> 00:43:30,160
Hello?

422
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:32,010
 Song Ah, where are you?  

423
00:43:32,010 --> 00:43:34,060
 You're on your way, right? 

424
00:43:34,060 --> 00:43:37,220
Huh? Where...

425
00:43:38,390 --> 00:43:40,080
 Is Friday okay? 

426
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:43,510
 Around 7:30? 

427
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:52,950
Ah, Dong Yoon. I'm really sorry, but...

428
00:44:22,550 --> 00:44:25,580
 Director Na has been discharged.  

429
00:44:40,710 --> 00:44:42,350
Yes, Joon Young?

430
00:44:42,350 --> 00:44:47,610
 Hello Director. I heard you have been discharged. 

431
00:44:47,610 --> 00:44:49,540
So you heard from Team Leader Cha.

432
00:44:49,540 --> 00:44:51,380
Yes.

433
00:44:51,380 --> 00:44:52,820
How are you feeling?

434
00:44:52,820 --> 00:44:55,320
I'm alright.

435
00:44:59,240 --> 00:45:01,480
That's a relief.

436
00:45:03,690 --> 00:45:06,260
It's truly a relief.

437
00:45:15,550 --> 00:45:17,790
Then please get some rest.

438
00:45:17,790 --> 00:45:22,060
Okay. Thank you for calling.

439
00:45:58,740 --> 00:46:01,180
What is it?

440
00:46:08,670 --> 00:46:10,480
That is...

441
00:46:14,180 --> 00:46:16,330
Listen, Dong Yoon.

442
00:46:17,980 --> 00:46:21,880
Many things have been happening to me today,

443
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:25,740
so I'm sorry, but could we talk next time?

444
00:46:25,740 --> 00:46:29,220
- Song Ah.  
 - Yeah.

445
00:46:30,180 --> 00:46:32,260
I like you.

446
00:46:35,220 --> 00:46:36,850
What?

447
00:46:40,120 --> 00:46:45,310
I... like you.

448
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:58,260
When I first saw you in the club room, and then became friends with you...

449
00:46:59,310 --> 00:47:02,160
I thought you were just a friend with whom I got along great.

450
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:09,440
But... at some point,

451
00:47:10,950 --> 00:47:13,670
I started to think of you all the time.

452
00:47:16,010 --> 00:47:23,050
This sounds cliche, but if I hastily confessed my feelings,

453
00:47:24,940 --> 00:47:27,880
we might not have been able to be friends anymore.

454
00:47:30,400 --> 00:47:32,800
I think that's what made me scared.

455
00:47:46,580 --> 00:47:48,970
Can you say some—

456
00:47:55,150 --> 00:47:57,490
What's wrong, Song Ah?

457
00:48:35,260 --> 00:48:37,910
Joon Young still looks the same, doesn't he?

458
00:48:37,910 --> 00:48:39,570
Oh, give that to me.

459
00:48:39,570 --> 00:48:43,180
I wanted to come near you and treat you to something tasty.

460
00:48:43,180 --> 00:48:47,240
No, it's fine. I wanted to come here, it's been so long.

461
00:48:47,240 --> 00:48:50,450
Thanks to that, I'm also here after a while.

462
00:48:50,450 --> 00:48:55,350
When the Director isn't here, we meet the important guests in this room.

463
00:48:58,880 --> 00:49:01,560
- Song Ah.  
 - Yes.

464
00:49:01,560 --> 00:49:07,250
For this semester, do you think you could help us while you attend university?

465
00:49:31,540 --> 00:49:33,600
Joon Young.

466
00:49:38,110 --> 00:49:40,420
What are you doing here?

467
00:49:43,890 --> 00:49:46,970
It's because you haven't come to practice yet.

468
00:49:51,540 --> 00:49:53,200
Let's talk for a bit.

469
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:55,810
What else do you want to say?

470
00:49:59,680 --> 00:50:02,090
Please be my accompanist.

471
00:50:03,380 --> 00:50:09,080
I told you I won't do it. I don't want to.

472
00:50:09,080 --> 00:50:10,780
It's all my fault.

473
00:50:10,780 --> 00:50:13,680
What did you do wrong? Huh?

474
00:50:13,680 --> 00:50:18,390
Do you even know what you did wrong? How can you come to me about this again?

475
00:50:20,830 --> 00:50:24,280
I shouldn't have done that to you in New York.

476
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:29,520
Do you know why I did it, that day?

477
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:33,350
I thought I was going mad, I felt so jealous.

478
00:50:34,840 --> 00:50:36,380
You were standing on that stage,

479
00:50:36,930 --> 00:50:40,150
so why did I have to be below it?

480
00:50:40,150 --> 00:50:43,020
while you were standing in the light...

481
00:50:46,560 --> 00:50:48,790
That's why I did that.

482
00:50:54,290 --> 00:50:56,860
I'm so childish, aren't I?

483
00:50:58,300 --> 00:51:03,290
But I really want to become a Seoryeong University professor.

484
00:51:04,360 --> 00:51:06,100
When people say to me...

485
00:51:06,100 --> 00:51:10,340
Like, "She's been surpassed."

486
00:51:13,090 --> 00:51:14,540
She was an unlucky prodigy.

487
00:51:14,540 --> 00:51:18,050
I really hate hearing that from other people.

488
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:24,110
That's why I want to be at Seoryeong University. Since it's a place that everyone recognizes.

489
00:51:31,600 --> 00:51:33,870
Joon Young, I...

490
00:51:35,780 --> 00:51:42,260
think about it every day... If I hadn't told you go to do the Chopin competition

491
00:51:43,530 --> 00:51:46,300
where would we be now?

492
00:51:49,630 --> 00:51:55,810
If I hadn't... wouldn't I be in a similar place to you, right now?

493
00:51:57,630 --> 00:52:00,770
If that was true, wouldn't it have been different?

494
00:52:03,910 --> 00:52:06,890
Wouldn't I be less miserable?

495
00:52:14,190 --> 00:52:18,250
So please help me. I'm begging you.

496
00:52:30,830 --> 00:52:34,790
   

497
00:52:39,540 --> 00:52:41,110
Hello?

498
00:52:41,110 --> 00:52:44,800
 Song Ah, have you been doing well? 

499
00:52:48,050 --> 00:52:49,790
Yes.

500
00:52:49,790 --> 00:52:51,840
 Are you at home? 

501
00:52:53,540 --> 00:52:55,760
No. I'm at the Kyunghoo building.

502
00:52:55,760 --> 00:52:59,100
 At Kyunghoo? Why are you there? 

503
00:52:59,100 --> 00:53:03,070
I came by to have lunch with Team Leader Cha

504
00:53:03,070 --> 00:53:06,380
and well... now I'm outside.

505
00:53:06,380 --> 00:53:10,400
 Then, Song Ah, please wait there for just one second. 

506
00:53:11,230 --> 00:53:12,990
Excuse me?

507
00:53:14,700 --> 00:53:15,790
Why?

508
00:53:15,790 --> 00:53:16,950
 There's something I want to tell you. 

509
00:53:16,950 --> 00:53:20,010
 Just wait there for one second. Just one second. 

510
00:53:31,900 --> 00:53:35,590
I told him I would wait and...

511
00:53:35,590 --> 00:53:40,660
I got all frustrated by myself and I think I spoiled everything.

512
00:53:43,460 --> 00:53:48,460
I didn't know that I lacked so much endurance...

513
00:53:49,650 --> 00:53:51,650
You're not.

514
00:53:51,650 --> 00:53:54,720
People who play instruments practice for hours daily for years

515
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:58,500
so diligently every single day.

516
00:53:58,500 --> 00:54:01,430
I believe in the strength of that time.

517
00:54:01,430 --> 00:54:05,800
So Song Ah, you're someone who knows how to endure.

518
00:54:08,260 --> 00:54:10,990
Believe in yourself.

